{
   "info" : "<table width=\"100%\" summary=\"page for chickwts\"><tr><td>chickwts</td><td style=\"text-align: right;\">R Documentation</td></tr></table>\n<h2>Chicken Weights by Feed Type</h2>\n<h3>Description</h3>\n<p>An experiment was conducted to measure and compare the effectiveness\nof various feed supplements on the growth rate of chickens.\n</p>\n<h3>Usage</h3>\n<pre>chickwts</pre>\n<h3>Format</h3>\n<p>A data frame with 71 observations on the following 2 variables.\n</p>\n<dl>\n<dt><code>weight</code></dt><dd><p>a numeric variable giving the chick weight.</p>\n</dd>\n<dt><code>feed</code></dt><dd><p>a factor giving the feed type.</p>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<h3>Details</h3>\n<p>Newly hatched chicks were randomly allocated into six groups, and each\ngroup was given a different feed supplement.  Their weights in grams\nafter six weeks are given along with feed types.\n</p>\n<h3>Source</h3>\n<p>Anonymous (1948)\n<em>Biometrika</em>, <b>35</b>, 214.\n</p>\n<h3>References</h3>\n<p>McNeil, D. R. (1977)\n<em>Interactive Data Analysis</em>.\nNew York: Wiley.\n</p>\n<h3>Examples</h3>\n<pre>\nrequire(stats); require(graphics)\nboxplot(weight ~ feed, data = chickwts, col = \"lightgray\",\n    varwidth = TRUE, notch = TRUE, main = \"chickwt data\",\n    ylab = \"Weight at six weeks (gm)\")\nanova(fm1 &lt;- lm(weight ~ feed, data = chickwts))\nopar &lt;- par(mfrow = c(2, 2), oma = c(0, 0, 1.1, 0),\n            mar = c(4.1, 4.1, 2.1, 1.1))\nplot(fm1)\npar(opar)\n</pre>\n",
